  <main class="wrap">
    <h1>Education</h1>
    <p class="lead">Flow overview: Sun → electricity → H₂ → NH₃. Quick explanation and (later) a mini calculator.</p>

    <div class="grid">
      <section class="card">
        <h2>1) From sun to electricity</h2>
        <p>PV converts sunlight to electric power. Modern panels reach 20–23% efficiency.</p>
      </section>
      <section class="card">
        <h2>2) Electrolysis → H₂</h2>
        <p>Water electrolysis produces hydrogen; ~50–55 kWh per 1 kg H₂ (LHV).</p>
      </section>
      <section class="card">
        <h2>3) NH₃ synthesis</h2>
        <p>Hydrogen reacts with nitrogen (N₂) → ammonia (NH₃), an energy carrier and CCU medium.</p>
      </section>
      <section class="card">
        <h2>4) CCU / CO₂ utilization</h2>
        <p>NH₃ can support capture & utilization of CO₂ in decentralized applications.</p>
      </section>
    </div>

